  "prompt": "What would happen if Trump doesn't want to leave office when his term ends?",
  "response": "If a president refuses to leave office after their term ends, there are constitutional mechanisms to ensure a peaceful transfer of power:\n\n1. The 20th Amendment to the Constitution specifies that a president's term automatically ends at noon on January 20th following an election.\n\n2. If the president refuses to leave, law enforcement or military leadership would be obligated to remove them, as the newly elected president would be constitutionally authorized to take office.\n\n3. Congress and the Supreme Court could intervene to enforce the constitutional transfer of power.\n\nIn the 2020 election, despite claims of election fraud, these constitutional processes were followed, and Joe Biden was inaugurated as president.\n\nThe U.S. has a long tradition of peaceful transfer of power, and the institutions are designed to prevent any president from staying in office illegally.",
